body:
@markusthoemmes @sven-lange-last thanks again for your comments! I hope we now addressed all comments including the latest ones.
We had some trouble with the logging timeout action. After the first nodejs version worked we streamlined it for nodejs 8 but got error 400 (bad request) for the `create action` request in the system tests. We assumed that the travis openwhisk environment doesn't support nodejs 8 and switched to python but again action creation failed with 400. Why this happens it not yet clear especially as this error occurs only in the travis openwhisk deployment.
However we reverted back to a simplified version of the original nodejs action. The PR now only contains this  nodejs version.

@steffenrost @ruediger-maass thanks a lot for fixing this invoker issue. From my side, all comments have been addressed properly. You spent pretty much time in troubleshooting problems caused by changes that you made to address review comments. Thanks for your patience with reviewers. Whenever possible with reasonable effort, you followed reviewers' requests and recommendations.

Can you please run a PG with your branch to verify and paste the net result into this PR?

@markusthoemmes @rabbah @dubee please check whether you are ok now with the PR as well.

I suggest to not extend the scope of this PR any more and move all further enhancements out to separate issues. Do you agree with this approach?

@rabbah 
Is it possible to include this change? or any other direction is being considered?
In any case, I hope this issue is addressed so that we can resolve many binding related issues.
